          "Limitations"
        ],
        [
          "Higher Education",
          "E-Learning",
          "Content-Based Filtering",
          "University courses to take next",
          "164,196 students in offline data; 70 undergrads in user study",
          "9,478 lecture courses → 7,487 after ≥20-enrollment filter",
          "Enrollment histories + catalog descriptions + course meta-info",
          "User gives one favorite course; models use learned embeddings (no special cold-start beyond that)",
          "Models/versioned on GitHub and refreshed 3× per semester after data refresh",
          "Remove generic sentences, stop words & punctuation; lemmatize/stem; tokenize; build TF, binary, tf-idf vectors",
          "Top-10 Recommendations (Max 1 per department)",
          "Offline: mean/median rank & recall@10 (equivalency); recall@1/@10 (analogies). User study: serendipity = mean(unexpectedness, successfulness); 6 dimensions rated",
          "BOW (div) scored highest in serendipity/novelty; course2vec best on analogies; RNN lacked novelty and often repeated requirement/major courses",
          "Students rely on catalog text; neural concepts may be hidden; hard to see commonality when descriptions are distal; real-time enrollment lag; future work: add latent semantics/syllabi"
        ]
      ],
      "index": 5
    }
  ],
